{
  "abstract": "A study was undertaken to know the difference/diversity between pigeonpea and its closely related wild\r\nspecies C. cajanifolius by studying their morphology, crossability, cytology of the hybrid between the two,\r\nand molecular studies. Studies revealed that there are at least 5–6 traits that separate the two species such as\r\nflower morphology, pod color and morphology, pod constriction, seed color and strophiole, 100 seed weight\r\nthat separate C. cajan from C. cajanifolius . Molecular studies revealed that a genetic dissimilarity index value\r\nranging from 0.81 to 0.94 exists between the two species.",
